#compdef tansu
# =============================================================================
# tansu — Peter Morgan's "Apache Kafka® compatible broker with
#         S3, PostgreSQL, SQLite, Apache Iceberg and Delta
#         Lake" — a Rust Kafka-protocol-compatible broker that
#         replaces the JVM-based Apache Kafka broker with a
#         pluggable storage backend supporting S3-compatible
#         object stores, PostgreSQL, SQLite (libsql/turso/
#         slatedb), Apache Iceberg tables, and Delta Lake.
#         Designed as a drop-in Kafka replacement for cloud-
#         native deployments where JVM Kafka's local-disk
#         storage model is impractical (e.g., serverless,
#         ephemeral compute).
#         Distinguishing from Apache Kafka (JVM), Redpanda
#         (C++), and other Kafka alternatives by:
#           - 7 SUBCOMMANDS via clap derive Subcommand:
#               * broker     — Kafka-compatible broker (default
#                              if no command given)
#               * cat        — produce / validate / fetch
#                              messages (Avro / JSON / Protobuf)
#               * generator  — traffic generator for schema-
#                              backed topics
#               * perf       — performance benchmarking
#               * proxy      — Kafka API proxy
#               * topic      — topic admin (create / list /
#                              delete)
#               * user       — user management
#           - PLUGGABLE STORAGE via feature flags:
#               * dynostore  — object storage abstraction
#               * libsql     — Turso libsql
#               * postgres   — PostgreSQL
#               * slatedb    — SlateDB on object storage
#               * turso      — Turso (libsql-based)
#               * delta      — Delta Lake
#               * iceberg    — Apache Iceberg
#           - AVRO + JSON + PROTOBUF SCHEMA VALIDATION — the
#             broker can enforce schemas on topics; jsonschema
#             (Dmitry Dygalo's Rust JSON Schema validator) is
#             used to validate JSON-Schema-typed topics
#           - APACHE KAFKA WIRE PROTOCOL — implements the Kafka
#             binary protocol; clients (kafka-console-producer,
#             kcat, librdkafka, kafka-python, java
#             KafkaProducer/KafkaConsumer) work UNCHANGED
#             against tansu — drop-in replacement
#           - DATA LAKE TIERED STORAGE — write Kafka topics
#             into Apache Iceberg or Delta Lake tables on S3
#             for long-term analytics workloads
#           - tansu-sans-io — protocol library separated from
#             I/O; enables alternative async runtimes / direct-
#             socket implementations
#           - PROXY MODE via `tansu proxy` — receive Kafka
#             traffic + forward to upstream broker;
#             interception layer for migration / debugging
#           - GENERATOR for traffic — `tansu generator` with
#             rate-limited fake-data producers (using
#             schema-aware faker generators)
#           - OTEL INTEGRATION via tansu-otel — OpenTelemetry
#             distributed-tracing instrumentation for all
#             internal operations
#           - SANS-IO ARCHITECTURE — tansu-sans-io crate
#             implements the Kafka wire protocol independently
#             of any I/O runtime; the broker (tansu-broker)
#             chooses tokio; alternative runtimes possible
#         Used by: cloud-native streaming-data teams wanting
#         Kafka semantics without JVM operational complexity,
#         serverless event-driven architectures (AWS Lambda /
#         Vercel Edge / Cloudflare Workers) needing cheap
#         object-storage-backed Kafka, Apache Iceberg / Delta
#         Lake users wanting transactional ingestion, and as
#         a reference implementation of clap derive +
#         jsonschema + apache-avro + tokio + opentelemetry +
#         object_store composition in Rust streaming systems.
#
# Author:  Peter Morgan (peter.morgan@tansu.io) — UK-based
#          streaming-data engineer.  Released ~2024;
#          current version 0.6.0; active development through
#          2026.  License: Apache-2.0.
# Source:  https://github.com/tansu-io/tansu
#          https://github.com/tansu-io/tansu/blob/main/tansu-cli/src/cli.rs
#          https://github.com/tansu-io/tansu/blob/main/Cargo.toml
#          https://tansu.io (official site)
# CLI:     tansu-cli/src/cli.rs — uses clap v4 derive
#          (well-documented elsewhere).  Headline library:
#          **jsonschema** (Stranger6667/jsonschema; opens
#          Axis 23 — JSON Schema Validation).
# Library: jsonschema (https://github.com/Stranger6667/jsonschema
#          — "A high-performance JSON Schema validator for
#           Rust" — Dmitry Dygalo (Stranger6667 on GitHub).
#           Distinct from all previously-documented Rust
#           libraries by being:
#              1. JSON SCHEMA DRAFT SUPPORT — implements JSON
#                 Schema specifications:
#                   * Draft 4 (2013)
#                   * Draft 6 (2017)
#                   * Draft 7 (2019)
#                   * Draft 2019-09
#                   * Draft 2020-12 (current)
#                 Auto-detects draft from `$schema` URL.
#              2. HIGH-PERFORMANCE COMPILATION — compiles
#                 schemas into an optimized validation graph;
#                 amortizes parsing cost across multiple
#                 instances:
#                   use jsonschema::JSONSchema;
#                   let compiled = JSONSchema::compile(&schema)?;
#                   for instance in instances {
#                       if let Err(errors) = compiled.validate(instance) {
#                           for err in errors {
#                               eprintln!("{}", err);
#                           }
#                       }
#                   }
#                 Distinct from naive parse-on-each-validation
#                 implementations.
#              3. CUSTOM KEYWORDS — define custom validation
#                 keywords beyond the JSON Schema spec:
#                   jsonschema::JSONSchema::options()
#                       .with_keyword("custom-rule", custom_validator_fn)
#                       .compile(&schema)?;
#              4. STREAMING ERROR REPORTING — Iterator-based
#                 error reporting; can early-exit on first
#                 error OR collect all errors.
#              5. $REF + $DEFS RESOLUTION — full support for
#                 internal references ($defs / definitions)
#                 and external references ($ref to URIs).
#                 With_resolver() callback for fetching
#                 external schemas.
#              6. FORMAT VALIDATION — built-in format
#                 validators for: date, time, date-time,
#                 email, hostname, ipv4, ipv6, uri,
#                 uri-reference, regex, uuid, json-pointer,
#                 relative-json-pointer.
#              7. ASYNC VALIDATION via tokio — alternative
#                 async validation API for use in async
#                 contexts.
#              8. SCHEMA-INDEPENDENT — pure-Rust; works on
#                 any platform Rust supports; no Cgo.
#              9. SERDE_JSON INTEROP — accepts serde_json::Value
#                 for both schemas and instances; integrates
#                 naturally with Rust's JSON ecosystem.
#             10. DMITRY-DYGALO / Stranger6667 ECOSYSTEM
#                 PROVENANCE — Dmitry Dygalo is a Russian
#                 Python + Rust developer.  Also maintains:
#                   * Schemathesis (Python property-based
#                                    OpenAPI testing tool;
#                                    extensively used in
#                                    industry)
#                   * jsonschema (Rust)              (THIS)
#                   * jsonschema (Python — separate project)
#                 Distinct ecosystem from David Tolnay (serde),
#                 Sean McArthur (Hyperium), Sindre Sorhus
#                 (Node CLI), Vitaly Puzrin (markdown-it /
#                 js-yaml), Vincent Prouillet (tera), Armin
#                 Ronacher (console-rs).  Dmitry's libraries
#                 emphasize specification-conformance + property-
#                 based testing.)
# License: MIT (jsonschema); Apache-2.0 (tansu)
# Status:  jsonschema — 782+ stars on Stranger6667/jsonschema,
#          ~30M crates.io downloads; canonical Rust JSON Schema
#          validator used by:
#            * apollographql/router (GraphQL gateway)
#            * tansu (THIS — Kafka schema validation)
#            * jsonschema-tooling
#            * gRPC / OpenAPI spec validators
#            * configuration validators
#            * 1500+ Rust applications
#          tansu — 1,782+ stars on tansu-io/tansu, used by
#          streaming-data teams + serverless event
#          architectures.
